  "text": "At this time, the gene therapy used different viral vector systems: based on adeno-, lenti-and retroviru-ses, herpes virus group and others. All these systems have limitations and drawbacks [CITATION_1] . Interest to baculoviruses as potential vectors of recombinant molecules is due to their ability to provide genetic transduction elements of significant size in mammalian cells and to control their expression and synthesis of large quantities of recombinant proteins [CITATION_2] .",
